pqML log



Version 2.0.0   Train on 100 items or 10,000--user's  choice.  Switching between
                the two will modify the model accordingly, mostly improving both
                but starting from a worse position.  Now REVERTS if model change
                unhelpful.Now exhausts change of 1 model char then leaves change
                and begins exhausting another;number of modified chars continues
                to grow but slow: not so wastefully as v1 but allows exhaustion.
                This gives better performance. Training on  100  still retrieves
                its items from the original 190kB Training_data file.
                Monday, December 26 2022

Version 1.0.1   Added time report for every model update.  Tested training on 20
                items and brought  misclassification down to 2 so it works well.
                Saturday, December 24 2022

Version 1.0.0   A voting kind of model-training system;  all  training items are
                run through the model in 1 pass then misclassification is logged
                and compared to another pass with a  modification  to the model.
                Improved models overwrite current model and changes to the model
                are never reverted. This way,  there is never  exhaustion, which
                would force each model character to be modified too deeply.
                Saturday, November 5 2022
